CHANGELOG.md
     1â†’# Changelog
     2â†’
     3â†’All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.
     4â†’
     5â†’The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/), and this
     6â†’project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).
     7â†’
     8â†’## [1.2.1] - 2025-10-26
     9â†’
    10â†’- Move more config to `pyproject.toml`, removed `setup.cfg`
    11â†’- Add support for reading `.env` from FIFOs (Unix) by [@sidharth-sudhir] in [#586]
    12â†’
    13â†’## [1.2.0] - 2025-10-26
    14â†’
    15â†’- Upgrade build system to use PEP 517 & PEP 518 to use `build` and `pyproject.toml` by [@EpicWink] in [#583]
    16â†’- Add support for Python 3.14 by [@23f3001135] in [#579](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/pull/563)
    17â†’- Add support for disabling of `load_dotenv()` using `PYTHON_DOTENV_DISABLED` env var. by [@matthewfranglen] in [#569]
    18â†’
    19â†’## [1.1.1] - 2025-06-24
    20â†’
    21â†’### Fixed
    22â†’
    23â†’* CLI: Ensure `find_dotenv` work reliably on python 3.13 by [@theskumar] in [#563](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/pull/563)
    24â†’* CLI: revert the use of execvpe on Windows by [@wrongontheinternet] in [#566](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/pull/566)
    25â†’
    26â†’
    27â†’## [1.1.0] - 2025-03-25
    28â†’
    29â†’**Feature**
    30â†’
    31â†’- Add support for python 3.13
    32â†’- Enhance `dotenv run`, switch to `execvpe` for better resource management and signal handling ([#523]) by [@eekstunt]
    33â†’
    34â†’**Fixed**
    35â†’
    36â†’- `find_dotenv` and `load_dotenv` now correctly looks up at the current directory when running in debugger or pdb ([#553] by [@randomseed42])
    37â†’
    38â†’**Misc**
    39â†’
    40â†’- Drop support for Python 3.8
    41â†’
    42â†’## [1.0.1] - 2024-01-23
    43â†’
    44â†’**Fixed**
    45â†’
    46â†’* Gracefully handle code which has been imported from a zipfile ([#456] by [@samwyma])
    47â†’* Allow modules using `load_dotenv` to be reloaded when launched in a separate thread ([#497] by [@freddyaboulton])
    48â†’* Fix file not closed after deletion, handle error in the rewrite function ([#469] by [@Qwerty-133])
    49â†’
    50â†’**Misc**
    51â†’* Use pathlib.Path in tests ([#466] by [@eumiro])
    52â†’* Fix year in release date in changelog.md ([#454] by [@jankislinger])
    53â†’* Use https in README links ([#474] by [@Nicals])
    54â†’
    55â†’## [1.0.0] - 2023-02-24
    56â†’
    57â†’**Fixed**
    58â†’
    59â†’* Drop support for python 3.7, add python 3.12-dev (#449 by [@theskumar])
    60â†’* Handle situations where the cwd does not exist. (#446 by [@jctanner])
    61â†’
    62â†’## [0.21.1] - 2023-01-21
    63â†’
    64â†’**Added**
    65â†’
    66â†’* Use Python 3.11 non-beta in CI (#438 by [@bbc2])
    67â†’* Modernize variables code (#434 by [@Nougat-Waffle])
    68â†’* Modernize main.py and parser.py code (#435 by [@Nougat-Waffle])
    69â†’* Improve conciseness of cli.py and __init__.py (#439 by [@Nougat-Waffle])
    70â†’* Improve error message for `get` and `list` commands when env file can't be opened (#441 by [@bbc2])
    71â†’* Updated License to align with BSD OSI template (#433 by [@lsmith77])
    72â†’
    73â†’
    74â†’**Fixed**
    75â†’
    76â†’* Fix Out-of-scope error when "dest" variable is undefined (#413 by [@theGOTOguy])
    77â†’* Fix IPython test warning about deprecated `magic` (#440 by [@bbc2])
    78â†’* Fix type hint for dotenv_path var, add StrPath alias (#432 by [@eaf])
    79â†’
    80â†’## [0.21.0] - 2022-09-03
    81â†’
    82â†’**Added**
    83â†’
    84â†’* CLI: add support for invocations via 'python -m'. (#395 by [@theskumar])
    85â†’* `load_dotenv` function now returns `False`. (#388 by [@larsks])
    86â†’* CLI: add --format= option to list command. (#407 by [@sammck])
    87â†’
    88â†’**Fixed**
    89â†’
    90â†’* Drop Python 3.5 and 3.6 and upgrade GA (#393 by [@eggplants])
    91â†’* Use `open` instead of `io.open`. (#389 by [@rabinadk1])
    92â†’* Improve documentation for variables without a value (#390 by [@bbc2])
    93â†’* Add `parse_it` to Related Projects (#410 by [@naorlivne])
    94â†’* Update README.md (#415 by [@harveer07])
    95â†’* Improve documentation with direct use of MkDocs (#398 by [@bbc2])
    96â†’
    97â†’## [0.20.0] - 2022-03-24
    98â†’
    99â†’**Added**
   100â†’
   101â†’- Add `encoding` (`Optional[str]`) parameter to `get_key`, `set_key` and `unset_key`.
   102â†’  (#379 by [@bbc2])
   103â†’
   104â†’**Fixed**
   105â†’
   106â†’- Use dict to specify the `entry_points` parameter of `setuptools.setup` (#376 by
   107â†’  [@mgorny]).
   108â†’- Don't build universal wheels (#387 by [@bbc2]).
