   241â†’## [0.10.5] - 2020-01-19
   242â†’
   243â†’**Fixed**
   244â†’
   245â†’- Fix handling of malformed lines and lines without a value (#222 by [@bbc2]):
   246â†’  - Don't print warning when key has no value.
   247â†’  - Reject more malformed lines (e.g. "A: B", "a='b',c").
   248â†’- Fix handling of lines with just a comment (#224 by [@bbc2]).
   249â†’
   250â†’## [0.10.4] - 2020-01-17
   251â†’
   252â†’**Added**
   253â†’
   254â†’- Make typing optional (#179 by [@techalchemy]).
   255â†’- Print a warning on malformed line (#211 by [@bbc2]).
   256â†’- Support keys without a value (#220 by [@ulyssessouza]).
   257â†’
   258â†’## 0.10.3
   259â†’
   260â†’- Improve interactive mode detection ([@andrewsmith])([#183]).
   261â†’- Refactor parser to fix parsing inconsistencies ([@bbc2])([#170]).
   262â†’  - Interpret escapes as control characters only in double-quoted strings.
   263â†’  - Interpret `#` as start of comment only if preceded by whitespace.
   264â†’
   265â†’## 0.10.2
   266â†’
   267â†’- Add type hints and expose them to users ([@qnighy])([#172])
   268â†’- `load_dotenv` and `dotenv_values` now accept an `encoding` parameter, defaults to `None`
   269â†’  ([@theskumar])([@earlbread])([#161])
   270â†’- Fix `str`/`unicode` inconsistency in Python 2: values are always `str` now. ([@bbc2])([#121])
   271â†’- Fix Unicode error in Python 2, introduced in 0.10.0. ([@bbc2])([#176])
   272â†’
   273â†’## 0.10.1
   274â†’- Fix parsing of variable without a value ([@asyncee])([@bbc2])([#158])
   275â†’
   276â†’## 0.10.0
   277â†’
   278â†’- Add support for UTF-8 in unquoted values ([@bbc2])([#148])
   279â†’- Add support for trailing comments ([@bbc2])([#148])
   280â†’- Add backslashes support in values ([@bbc2])([#148])
   281â†’- Add support for newlines in values ([@bbc2])([#148])
   282â†’- Force environment variables to str with Python2 on Windows ([@greyli])
   283â†’- Drop Python 3.3 support ([@greyli])
   284â†’- Fix stderr/-out/-in redirection ([@venthur])
   285â†’
   286â†’
   287â†’## 0.9.0
   288â†’
   289â†’- Add `--version` parameter to cli ([@venthur])
   290â†’- Enable loading from current directory ([@cjauvin])
   291â†’- Add 'dotenv run' command for calling arbitrary shell script with .env ([@venthur])
   292â†’
   293â†’## 0.8.1
   294â†’
   295â†’-   Add tests for docs ([@Flimm])
   296â†’-   Make 'cli' support optional. Use `pip install python-dotenv[cli]`. ([@theskumar])
   297â†’
   298â†’## 0.8.0
   299â†’
   300â†’-   `set_key` and `unset_key` only modified the affected file instead of
   301â†’    parsing and re-writing file, this causes comments and other file
   302â†’    entact as it is.
   303â†’-   Add support for `export` prefix in the line.
   304â†’-   Internal refractoring ([@theskumar])
   305â†’-   Allow `load_dotenv` and `dotenv_values` to work with `StringIO())` ([@alanjds])([@theskumar])([#78])
   306â†’
   307â†’## 0.7.1
